# Phase V — Rebecca Brewer Editorial Assessment (October 2021)

---

## 2021-10-01 — Editorial Letter Delivered

The most important document in the Keeper archive.

Core diagnosis:

1. Pace too fast in first half
2. Stakes unclear scene-to-scene
3. Emotional spine diffused
4. POV transitions confusing
5. Worldbuilding insufficiently grounded

Praise:

- Strong prose
- Strong dialogue
- Compelling protagonist
- One of best written manuscripts she’d read recently

But:

The book is not yet structurally complete.

---

## Key Structural Critiques

- Prologue voice disconnected
- Wynn’s jump reads like attempted murder
- Abbajay second-night scene reads like assault
- Characters read younger than 15
- Readers need stronger establishing shots
- Target word count closer to 100k

This is not a surface-level fix.

It is architecture.

---

## 2021-10-30 — Family Forward

Evan forwards the letter to inner circle.

> "Very validating. I knew 80% of this to be true."

One minute later:

> "Just know that I will see this through."

Resolve resets.

---

## 2021-11-14 — “Experimental Mode”

Six weeks later.

> "I’m in a very experimental mode that I want to stay in for now."

He delays the call.

He is rebuilding internally.

---

## 2021-12-07 — Editorial Debrief

Call happens.

No documentation of content.

But aftermath visible in behavior.

---

## 2021-12-29 — Codex Backup (Not Manuscript)

Attachment:
TKT Codex.scrivx

This is critical.

For the first time, the backup is not the novel.
It’s the world bible.

Energy shift complete.

The obsession has moved from prose → worldbuilding.

